column5: There really seems to be pattern as to who makes them go hill in a hurry too.  Quite irritating.
Heard a rumour a 61 inch long muskie was reported  and later pulled from a musky site this weekend.Does anyone have any details?
I know what everybody is thinking. No, it wasn't me.
I dont catch little ones like that...  so it was not me.
That could very well be true....if so congrats to the lucky angler!!  Just wasn't me..   RFS
The last one I caught seems to be getting closer to that mark every time I tell the story!
the only SKI I have ever caught that was that long had bindings and a waxy finish on the bottom.
my best two added together this year may not make that mark.

aparently a 61 inch pike was also caught...    http://www.gofishing.co.uk/Angling-Times/S...ld-record-pike/  so far in the last couple weeks:  new record rainbow new record brown new record pike (from last winter?)  giant alligator gars, make people fear for their lives in hong kong.. http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/classified-odd/...hong-kong-ponds  the fishing news keeps going on!  I should be on the water...
The full story is on musky hunter now .wish I knew how to make a link or even attach the pic.scary big.
Here ya go Wes!     Guess I was a little late!  Congrats to the new Musky God!
Wow.
NICE
Looks like a 59 1/2" to me!!!   ... where's the measuring tape???
Graham, is that you?
Thats a monster to be sure.
GB and Tim, thanks.She's a" chunky monkey" huh?
... and "short" as well!!
coach your messed, but some of the stuff you say is.......funny, sometimes a little out of hand but funny.

Have you seen how musky posts (among others) go down hill here sometimes? The question of length (never trust a guy about that in the first place) and proper handling are the top 2 reasons a musky post goes sour.
I think the steehead topics go downhill faster.I heard that steelhead dont actually eat marshmallows.
You're wrong Bubba Joe... steelhead and salmon LOVE the marshmallows!!!
They love marshmellows, and earplugs!!!!
